    "name": "SEAL",
    "description": "The approach involves studying heuristic learning for link prediction by extracting a local subgraph around a target link and learning a function that maps these subgraph patterns to link existence, thereby automatically creating network-suited heuristics. This framework is supported by two components: first, the development of a novel $\\gamma$-decaying heuristic theory, which unifies various existing heuristics and proves they can be well approximated from local subgraphs. Second, based on this $\\gamma$-decaying theory, a new method utilizes a graph neural network (GNN) to learn these heuristics directly from local subgraphs. Experimentally, this GNN-based method achieved unprecedented performance across a wide range of problems.",
    "keywords": [
        "Link prediction",
        "heuristic learning",
        "local subgraphs",
        "γ-decaying theory",
        "graph neural network (GNN)"
    ],
